						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying near the Śiva temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>Kākatīya: Pratāparudradēva.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of the grazing fees <hi rend="italic">(pullari)</hi> of the village of Ākurājupalli to the temple of Tripurāntakadēva by a certain Āyakapediṁgāru, at the instance of 72 <hi rend="italic">niyōgas,</hi> for the merit of the king.</p>						

